description: Charlie Morton combined with three relievers on a five-hitter and the Atlanta Braves beat Nathan Eovaldi and the Texas Rangers 5-2 for their sixth straight win.
title: Morton throws 6 strong innings and d'Arnaud hits another homer as streaking Braves top Rangers 5-2

description: From start to finish, Emerance Maschmeyer was Ottawa’s best player making 35 saves in a 4-0 win over Minnesota on Saturday night.
title: Emerance Maschmeyer stops 35 and Brianne Jenner has a hat trick as Ottawa beats Minnesota 4-0

description: Tyler Stephenson hit his first career grand slam in the first inning, Stuart Fairchild drove in two runs and the Cincinnati Reds beat the Los Angeles Angels 7-5 to take the first two games of the three-game interleague series.
title: Stephenson hits 1st career grand slam, Fairchild drives in 2 as the Reds beat the Angels 7-5

description: Helen Maroulis, the first American woman to win a wrestling gold medal, also became the first U.S. female wrestler to qualify for three Summer Games as she earned a spot Saturday night on the American team for Paris.
title: Helen Maroulis becomes first US female wrestler to qualify for three Olympic teams

description: Zack Wheeler pitched no-hit ball for 7 1/3 innings, Brandon Marsh homered and the Philadelphia Phillies extended their winning streak to five by beating the struggling Chicago White Sox 9-5.
title: Zack Wheeler has no-hit bid for 7 1/3 innings as Phillies beat slumping White Sox 9-5

description: Jalen Brunson and Josh Hart each scored 22 points, Deuce McBride led a huge effort by New York’s backups with 21 and the Knicks beat the Philadelphia 76ers 111-104 in Game 1 of their Eastern Conference first-round series.
title: Knicks beat 76ers 111-104 in Game 1 of playoffs. Brunson and Hart score 22 points and backups star

description: Josh Naylor hit a two-run homer and celebrated by striking himself on the helmet with his bat, providing the Cleveland Guardians with the go-ahead run in a 6-3 victory over the Oakland Athletics.
title: Josh Naylor hits a two-run HR and himself with his bat, helping the Guardians beat the Athletics 6-3

description: Nikola Jokic arrived in character for a first-round playoff game Saturday night. That character was “Gru,” the protagonist from the “Despicable Me” movies.
title: In character: Nuggets big man Nikola Jokic shows up to game dressed like "Gru" from "Despicable Me"

description: Anthony Edwards drained a 3-pointer from the wing in a dominant third quarter for the Minnesota Timberwolves and nodded his head as he barked and stared at Kevin Durant on the retreat up the court.
title: Anthony Edwards gets the best of his favorite player Kevin Durant in Timberwolves' win over Suns

description: Nelly Korda was one shot off the lead at the Chevron Championship when the third round was suspended Saturday because of lightning in the area.
title: Korda 1 stroke back in suspended 3rd round of Chevron Championship as she chases 5th straight win

description: Toronto Maple Leafs forward William Nylander was scratched from the team's playoff opener with an undisclosed injury that developed between the end of the regular season and Game 1 of the first-round series against Boston.
title: Toronto's Nylander out for Game 1 against Bruins

description: A Michigan sheriff says a young brother and sister died and several people were injured, several seriously, when a vehicle driven by a suspected drunken driver crashed into a child's birthday party Saturday at a boat club.
title: Vehicle crashes into party, killing brother and sister and injuring 15, sheriff says

description: Police in New York City say a knife attack on a crowded party boat at a pier in Brooklyn has resulted in the hospitalization of three people.
title: 3 hospitalized after knife attack on party boat in New York City, along East River in Brooklyn
